                    <h4>The Gladiator Guide</h4>
                    <hr>
                    <div>
                        <article>
<div>
<div>Hello. I know there are a lot of useful threads out there, but none of which you can call a "guide". So here I am making one.<br /><br /><strong style="font-size: medium;"><br /></strong><span style="font-size: large;"><strong>Skills<br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: small;">Let's start with the skill descriptions. I'm only going to describe the skills you get while changing to Gladiator apprenticeship and further.<br /><br /></span><strong style="font-size: small;">Double attack (passive)</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Chance to attack enemy twice.<br /></span><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><u>Edit:</u>&nbsp;since there has been a numerous amount of questions about autoskills, be aware that double attack "kills" EVERY autoskill which activates by attack when it engages (the only exception is HP&amp;MP regen chance by attack/damage skill from Bloodthirst).<br /></span><span style="font-size: small;">SLv4 Gladiator apprentice (normal damage x1.8)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv5 (Book - Delma - Lograth City) (Lv240) (normal damage x2)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv6 (Quest - King Elbano - Capital City Eldan [Echipo x50, Farzan x50, Knight Hair Ornament x1, Hard Water x30]) (Lv320) (normal damage x2.3)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Warcry </strong><span style="font-size: small;">- Raises MaxHP and ATK</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 MP128 (Gladiator apprentice) (ATK+16% MaxHP+16% 4 minutes duration)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv4 MP160 (Quest - Delma - Lograth City [Mob Piteco x60, Manitari x30, Polished Hide x6, Warm Fur x3]) (Lv260) (ATK+20% MaxHP+20% 5 minutes duration)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Relax (passive)</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Raises auto HP and MP recovery</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 (Full gladiator) (HP natural recovery +30, MP natural recovery +15)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv4 (Book - Sitara - Kreya City) (Lv260) (HP natural recovery +? MP natural recovery +?)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Berserk</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Converts all of your remaining MP into full out attack rush (duration depends on current mp left) (pretty much useless after you get tempest)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP150 (all MP) (Quest - Levia - Port Spargas Pub [Meanae x50 Lantern Ghost x50, Gator Samurai x50, Kyon x50]) (Lv160)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Sword mastery (passive)</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Gain knowledge about the handling of the sword. Raises ATK and hit rate when wielding sword.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 (Gladiator apprentice)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 (Full gladiator)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 (Book - Filely - Eryldan Desert) (Lv200)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Astute</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Attack enemy with a sharp blow. Power is dependent on the critical damage. Procs dizzy by chance (proc rate depends on DEX). Requires -5s skill delay for spam.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP32 (Gladiator apprentice) (about 1.5 times the critical damage)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP48 (Full gladiator) (about 2.0 times the critical damage)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 MP64 (Book - Matif - Drafbourg) (Lv200) (about 2.5 times the critical damage)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv4 MP80 (Book - Sitara - Kreya City) (Lv300) (about three times the critical damage)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Cross counter </strong><span style="font-size: small;">- Counterattack the enemy upon receiving a hit, deals the same damage as your normal critical hit (it can't double attack and it doesn't work if you evade the attack)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP36 (Full gladiator) (duration 5 minutes)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP28 (Quest - King Elbano - Capital City Elban [Orc x30 Malfil x30, Poisonous Claw x15, Strange Spine x30, Sky Dragon Horn x1]) (Lv160) (effect time of 7 minutes)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 MP20 (Book - Sitara - Kreya City) (Lv260) (effect time of 9 minutes)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Penetrate</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Raises ATK power, recoils the damage dealt a bit. At skill level 3 the recoil is cancelled.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP52 (Full gladiator) (ATK +5% recoil+2%, 7 minutes duration)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP65 (Quest - Levia - Port Spargas Pub [Obligaus x1 Fire Spirit x40, Water Spirit x40, Wind Spirit x40, Earth Spirit x40]) (Lv220) (ATK +7% recoil+1% 8 minutes duration)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv3 MP78 (Quest - King Elbano - Capital City Eldan [Parazaia x1 Death Ent x60, Little Devils Nail x5, Sharp Claw x5]) (Lv300) (ATK +?% Effect time of ? minutes)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Solid Skin</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Gives you second layer of HP based on your STR (amount of STR points x20 basically). Very useful skill, similar to enchy's stone skin. Reduces piercing damage by half when the skill finishes.<br /></span>SLv1 MP100 (Quest - Saterica City Pub) (Lv150)<br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Regenerate</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Regenerates your HP, consumes 1 gladiator revita (you can use it without it but then your HP drops by half and the duration is shorter)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP1 (Quest - Levia - Port Spargas Pub [Cobalt x1, Fearful Evil Eye x20, Blazing Hellfire x40, Hard Bark x40]) (Lv180) (up to HP about 5 percent of the recovery effect time in 5-second intervals of 2 minutes)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP1 (Book - Sitara- Kreya City) (Lv280) (up to HP about 6% in 4-second intervals recovery effect time of 2 minutes)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Esperanza</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Greatly increases your ATK power and DEF for 1 minute, reduces EVA to 1. After it wears off it leaves you with exhaustion (greatly decreases ATK/DEF).</span><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Edit: now that Bloodthirst has been patched you can pretty much keep your esperanza up for the entire time, as Bloodthirst now gives you Exhaustion Nullification effect.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP300 (Quest - Levia - Port Spargas Pub [Mezzaluna x1 Zimov x1, Dead Bones x20, Peppercorn x50]) (Lv180) (ATK + STR &times; 1.0 effect time of 60 seconds fatigue state 60 seconds)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv2 MP330 (Quest - Matif - Drafbourg [Megaroche x60 Balor x60, Fine Needle x40, Reflex Pill x20]) (Lv240) (ATK + STR &times; 1.1 effect time of 60 seconds fatigue state 50 seconds)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Sword Tempest&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size: small;">- Damage skill, aoe, gives you attack speed buff and Tempest gauge which gives you more EVA and melee pierce the more % you have. At 90% or more it halves your attack speed (berserk/interfike aspd). Consumes 1% of your HP upon activation. The duration of ASPD buff depends on your skill delay. Requires -5 seconds delay for spam (also doesn't give you ASPD buff while in exhaustion state). Deals more damage when attacking multiple enemies. AGI impacts this skill heavily, adding both massive damage and evasion boosts to the skill.</span><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Edit: the skill got patched in one of the recent updates, the damage got boosted slightly and maximum amount of Tempest has been raised to 150%.<br />Edit 2: 275 is no longer the cap for damage boost. AGI now increases Tempest damage indefinitely.<br /></span><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP10 (Quest - Matif - Drafbourg [Draco x80 Lutor x40, High Ent x20, Beelzenoid x1]) (Lv220) (effect time of 8 seconds)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Pillar Blade</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Damage skill, aoe, deals higher damage than your normal critical hit. Inflicts bleeding status on enemy if it's dizzy (bleeding damage based on STR). Requires -2s skill delay for spam.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 MP12 (Quest - Levia - Port Spargas Pub [Sianas x1 Hard Goblin x50, Pagron x25, Black Metal Bit x50]) (Lv200)</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">Bloodthirst</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Active skill, needs at least 85% of tempest gauge to activate it, leaves you with 10% after activation. In exchange it gives you skill&amp;item delay reduction (-1.5s), HP&amp;MP recovery chance by attack and by skills (yes, it can proc on every damage skill). The duration depends on your current HP left, the less the better. On boss fights it's best to switch gears to get more maxhp, activate it and then switch back to your normal gears.</span><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Edit: Bloodthirst has been patched in one of the most recent updates, it now gives you Exhaustion Nullification effect with duration as long as your Combative effect. It still needs at least 85% of tempest for activation, but now the amount of Tempest you are left with after activation depends on how much Tempest you have during the activation (drops by 85% each use).<br /></span>SLv1 MP? (Quest - Delma - Lograth City [Calmo x30 Zazel x1, Ape's Rag x30, Crystal Eye x30] (Lv260)<br /><strong style="font-size: small;"><br />Job mastery (passive)</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Job bonus is improved.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">SLv1 (Quest - King Elbano - Capital City Eldan [Aleek x60 Pincer x60, Mountain Dragon Shell x1, Apatite x30]) (Lv280)<br /><br /></span><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>Volunteer </strong>-&nbsp;Raises spirit depending on bravery. Large bonus to tempest. Has cooldown time. (Effect: +100% tempest gauge, 30 sec "Recast" debuff)<br />SLv1 (Book - Sitara - Kreya City [Courage and Bravery 1]) (Lv320) (7M Spina)<br /><br /><strong>Hervorhild&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;Become the guardian of troops of refined skill. Greatly decrease damage to allies. (Consumes 85% tempest gauge)<br />SLv1 (Quest - King Elbano - Elban [Cellect: Miasma Crystal Fragment x1, Dragon's Blood x2, Raging Gale x5, Unextinguishable Spark x5] (Lv340)<br /><br /><strong>Valkyrie Blade&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;Swing the Valkyrie's sword. Consumes tempest and deals big DMG to enemies. (Uses 85% tempest gauge. Single target dmg that also ignores barriers)<br /></span>SLv1 (Quest - King Elbano - Elban [Kill: Herja (x30) Angel Luna (x30); Collect:&nbsp;Light Sword Handguard (x1) Sparkling Matter (x30)] (Lv340)<br /><br /><br /><span style="color: #e61b19; font-size: small;">Big thanks to <a title="@sasorro" href="/user/1046">Sasorro</a> for his thread:&nbsp;<a href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/30255/new-320-340-skill-quest" target="_blank" rel="noopener norewrite">irunaonline.boards.net/thread/30255/new-320-340-skill-quest</a></span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: large;"><br />Builds</strong><br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><strong style="font-size: small;">STR=CRT&gt;VIT</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Probably the most common build around. Deals less damage than other builds, but is very tanky and useful at low levels.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pros:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-tanky</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-probably the best solo mob grinder among other builds (with bloodthirst you pretty much don't even have to bother casting solid skin)</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-with recent skill adjustments it's now seriously (SERIOUSLY) hard to kill as long as you manage to keep your Esperanza up</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Cons:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-lowest damage</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-low evasion</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-less wanted in parties at higher levels</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-chugs potions like a junkie if you don't use bloodthirst (or if you don't pt a bishop)<br /></span></span>There's so many stat points to spend nowadays that this build should not even be considered an option as an endgame build anymore. You can build up vit but it's not the main stat you should focus on, especially with all the resistance gear available.<br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">STR=CRT&gt;AGI*</strong><strong style="font-size: small;">&gt;VIT</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Build with balanced damage and survival. Deals higher tempest damage than previous build (i mean, a lot higher), but can take less beating.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pros:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-high evasion</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-high tempest damage</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-decent hp pool</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-one of the "endgame" builds</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Cons:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-doesn't offer the highest DPS available<br /></span>-outclassed by non vit builds<br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">STR=CRT&gt;DEX&gt;VIT</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Build with guaranteed skill delay reduction and some VIT to make up for lack of evasion.</span><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Edit: the soon-to-be-released valkyrie blade will significantly up the DPS of this build, especially if you have invested points in <strong>RDL</strong></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pros:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-deals highest pillar blade and astute damage</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-high dizzy proc chance from astute</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-DEX grants additional skill delay reduction</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Cons:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-low evasion</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-still needs skill delay gears, DEX isn't everything</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-tempest damage not as high as with AGI builds</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-fragile without resistance gear</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: small;">STR=CRT&gt;AGI*</strong><strong style="font-size: small;">&gt;DEX</strong><span style="font-size: small;"> - Build with highest damage in game, not recommended at low levels, great for party players</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Pros:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-deals highest tempest damage, high pillar and astute damage</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-high evasion</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-high dizzy proc rate from astute</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-DEX grants additional skill delay reduction</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Cons: </span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">-low survival</span><span style="font-size: small;"><br /><br /><u>*As AGI got buffed, 275 AGI is no longer the cap damage boost for Tempest. It now benefits from AGI no matter the amount.</u><br /><br /></span>Additional stats:&nbsp;<br /><strong>RDL </strong>- useful if you have red/yellow lines in your apostolia, but don't invest in it if you're underleveled, since the bonus isn't as high as from the conventional (non-apostolia) stats. If you plan to invest points in that, save it for the last.<br /><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">A quick overview of what affects what:<br />STR - ATK, Solid Skin amount, Bleeding damage, overall skill damage<br />VIT - Max HP, DEF, MDEF<br />AGI - EVA, Tempest damage, Tempest EVA gain (prevents from skill spam, but there are workarounds for that, see Tips and Tricks section)<br />DEX - Dizzy proc chance (from Astute), ATK, Accuracy (not important), Pillar Blade skill delay, overall skill delay (reduction isn't that high, so it's not wise to go for DEX as a third stat just because of the -SD)<br />CRT - CRT chance, CRT damage, overall skill damage</span><br /><strong><br /><span style="font-size: large;">Equipment</span><br /></strong><span style="font-size: small;">Most of the equipment descriptions are copied from JP wiki, so forgive me for messy translations. Also not every equip is here, so if you want me to add something to the list please provide me with stats. I'll skip most of the HP gears and only list the gears with beneficial stats.<br /></span><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Popular/top tier equipment will be <u>underlined</u>&nbsp;so people can see them as a reference &amp; know what stats to search for when gearing up.</span><span style="font-size: small;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><u>Side note</u>: Keep in mind most of the stuff listed here is interchangeable between all of the builds, different build doesn't necessarily mean different equipment.</span><br /><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Edit: I have "translated" some of the descriptions so it's easier to read through them. Also I took several descriptions from iruna-online.info , so there might be some mistakes (although I'm trying to constantly update the guide to get rid of them).</span><br /><strong><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Swords</span></strong><span style="font-size: small;">:<br /><strong><u>Fallen God's Sword</u></strong>&nbsp;- ATK: 320~&nbsp;Dark Element, MaxHP&amp;MP-5%, ATK +16%, Melee to Boss +2%. When attacking, probability of... When equipped with the devil's armor...<br /><strong><u>Legacy of Will II</u></strong><strong> - </strong>ATK: 293+ DEF: 10 ATK +18%, MaxHP &amp; MaxMP +15%, Accuracy +15%, Evasion +20%, Melee pierce +18%, Item recovery +15%, ATK up by AGI a little<br /><strong><u>Sauro Blade L5</u></strong> - ATK: 310-315 ATK +5% Critical damage +19%, Heal reward +8%, STR +10, VIT +10, Item delay -1.7 seconds, Melee +400, Melee pierce +5% (Hidden: Magic &amp; Melee resistance +1% for every 20 STR)<br /><strong><u>Air Strum III</u></strong> - ATK: ? Melee to Neutral +25% ATK +8% Skill Delay -1.4s Item Delay -0.7s Range +1<br /><strong>Futsu no Mitama</strong> - ATK: 260-275 All elements, ATK + 8%, Delay -0.5 seconds<br /><strong>Kloff Pillar</strong> - ATK: 255-264 DEF: 5 Melee pierce +5%, ASPD -20%, ATK +16%, Flame element, Small ATK up by VIT, Additional attack chance<br /><strong>Freesia Sword</strong>&nbsp;<strong>II</strong>-&nbsp;ATK 281-286 Melee +22% to Fire, Melee -22% to Water, ATK +12%, MaxHP +10%, Critical damage +10%, Magic counter chance<br /><strong>Sea Breeze II -</strong>&nbsp;ATK: 296+ ATK +15%, MaxMP +15%, Autoskills +8%, Absolute evasion +10%, Wind element, if AGI &gt; 299 Melee +5% to Water<br /><strong>Emerald Roar II</strong> -&nbsp;ATK: 299+ DEF: 12 Earth element, ATK +17%, MaxHP +15%, Wind R +5%, Paralyze +6%, CRT +13, Melee R +7%<br /><strong>Accord Sword</strong> -&nbsp;ATK: 279-293 DEF: 15 Light element, Melee R +10%, Autoskill +7%, Small STR by INT, Magic attack chance by attack<br /><strong>Claiomh solais III</strong> -&nbsp;ATK: 311+ Magic R +14%, Item delay -1 second, CRT up by CRT, Light element<br /><strong>Blue Moon Sword</strong> -&nbsp;ATK: 250-265 ATK up by CRT, Magic R +10%, Dark Element<br /><strong>Red Tengu IV</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;ATK: 315~ Evasion +16%, Critical damage +19%, ASPD -10%, Melee up based on STR, Small Melee pierce up by Lv (around 1.5 times the Lv)<br /><strong>Lamia IV</strong>&nbsp;- ATK: 304~ DEF: 4 Dark element, ATK + 8%, Magic Resistance + 12%, MaxMP - 20%, HP recovery chance by attacking, ASPD + 10%, Autoskill + 8%<br /><strong>Gold Rex III</strong> - ATK: 305~ DEF: 2 ATK +9%, Critical damage +14%, stun time -1 second, Auto HP &amp; MP recovery +30%<br /><strong>Fuguhiki Knife</strong> - ATK: 260-275 Melee +30% to Water, Melee pierce -30% if DEX &lt; 300, ASPD +20% (only use this if you have really high DEX)<br /><strong>Rock Sword Varuten&nbsp;</strong>- ATK: 311~ DEF: 9 Gaia element, Critical rate +50, Magic evasion +7%, DEF up by STR<br /><strong>Nenekirimaru</strong> - ATK: ~279 ATK +16%, AGI +10, ASPD -20%, Melee pierce up by DEX<br /><strong>Inslector </strong>-&nbsp;ATK: 290 DEF: 10&nbsp;Skill delay +1 sec, Melee +25% to Neutral, ATK +15%, Range Cut +10%, Hate +20%, Melee counter chance<br /><strong>Vermilion IV</strong> - ATK: ? MaxHP + 30%, Rate reduction + 17%, Physical + 30%, STR and basic ASPD ATK increase / decrease<br /><strong>Lion King's Sword</strong> - ATK: 285+ Flame Element, Critical Damage +15%, ATK +5%, When you meet a certain condition...&nbsp;<br /><br /><strong>Armors</strong>:<br /><strong><u>Fallen God's Armor</u>&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;ATK: 5 DEF: 30 MaxHP&amp;MP - 10%, Light Res - 50%, Dark Res + 20%, ATK&amp;MATK + 14%, When equipped with the devil 's weapons...<br /><u style="font-weight: bold;">Ultimi</u> (strenghtened 2)&nbsp;- DEF: 23-28 ATK + 12%, MATK + 16%, Critical up, Delay -1 second, Accuracy+100, Absolute evasion + 10%, Melee +600<br /><strong><u>Bellow of Order</u></strong>-DEF: 25-29&nbsp;Melee and Magic R +12%, ATK up by STR, MATK up by INT, Skill delay -1 sec, Damage cut chance by defense<br /><strong>Schwermer </strong>(strenghtened 2)&nbsp;-&nbsp;DEF: 20-26 Critical Damage + 16%, Autoskill + 5%, VIT + 9, Skill Delay - 1 sec, Damage nullification chance by defense<br /><strong>Exelis </strong>(strenghtened 3)<strong> - </strong>DEF: 19~ ATK: 20 ATK +8% MATK +8% Evasion +15% Magic R +13% Skill delay -1.8 sec<strong><br />Hulam Ries</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened 2) -&nbsp;DEF: 11-17 ATK: 25 ATK +11%, Melee pierce +20%, STR +5, CRT +10, MaxHP +2000, Item delay -1.4 seconds, proportion mitigation +5%<br /><strong>Ira </strong>(strenghtened 2)&nbsp;-&nbsp;DEF: 15-18 ATK: 25 ATK +16% Magic evasion +10%, Critical rate +25%, Autoskill +10%, Critical damage +7%, Melee +1%, Melee R -25%<br /><strong>Dragon Mail</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened 2) - DEF: 18-24 ATK: 15 ATK +9%, MATK +10%, Critical rate +15, Critical damage +8%, Melee and Magic R +6%, Absolute accuracy +15%, Autoskill +5%<br /><strong>Heinrich mail</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened 2) - DEF: 28 ATK +14%, MATK +14%, Melee pierce +6%, Magic pierce +6%, Magic evasion +8%, Heal reward +1000, Damage cut if HP is under 25% or lower<br /><strong>Shiroito Odoshi</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened 2) - DEF: 16-21 ATK: 25 Critical rate +22 with Swords, Item recovery +25%, ATK +6%, VIT +10, AGI +9<br /><br /><strong>Additional Gears</strong>:<br /><u style="font-weight: bold;">Fallen God's Helm</u>-&nbsp;ATK: 10 DEF: 25&nbsp;Light Res -10%, Dark Res + 5%, ATK + 12%, Melee&amp;Magic Res + 8%, Critical Damage + 8%. When equipped with Devil's Armor ...<br /><span style="font-weight: bold;"><u>Force Helm </u></span>(strenghtened 2) - DEF: 5 ATK: 33 ATK +5%, Critical damage +13%, Hate rise +10%, Melee R +10%, Magic R +10%, CRT +10<br /><u><strong>Monty Beret</strong></u> (strenghtened) - DEF: 17-18 Melee R +8%, Magic R +8%, Skill delay -1.2 seconds, Absolute accuracy +9%, ATK up by DEX, Item recovery +25%, ATK +9%<br /><strong>Separation arrows</strong> (strenghtened)&nbsp;-&nbsp;DEF: 0-5 ATK: 15 MaxHP -10%, ATK +6%, Delay -0.6 sec, Critical Damage +12%.&nbsp;During White Day event, probability of physical attack.<br /><strong>Barbarotita</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened 2) - DEF: 19 ATK: 23 ATK +14%, STR +10, Skill delay -1.2 seconds, Accuracy rate -15%, Stun time -1 sec<br /><strong>Arelta</strong>&nbsp;(strenghtened) - DEF: 22-25 ATK &middot; MATK + 7 %, Absolute&amp;Magic evasion + 6%, MaxHP + 15%, MP natural recovery + 20%, critical rate +20, skill delay -1 seconds<br /><strong>Medim Corona </strong>(strenghtened 2)&nbsp;-&nbsp;DEF: 18 Melee up by 350% of Lv, ATK +6%, Critical damage +10% with Swords, CRT +5, Range +2 with Claws, Melee Pierce +5%<br /><strong>Evil Dragon Wings</strong> - DEF: 0-3 Skill Delay -2s (very useful if you need that extra skill delay on the budget)<br /><strong>Knight of Honor</strong> - ATK: 5 DEF: 1 Skill delay -0.5 s, Item delay -0.8 s, Absolute evasion -50%, Magic evasion -50%, KO +3 s, VIT +15, ATK +9%, MaxHP +22%, Crt up<br /><strong>Blocachnez</strong> - ATK: 15 DEF: 14 Critical rate +10, Critical damage +10%, MaxHP +15%, Recoil +30%, If STR &gt; 256, then Recoil -30%, Critical damage +10%<br /><strong>Rebellion Mask</strong> (strenghtened 2) -&nbsp;ATK: 34 DEF: 12-18 CRT + 30, MP Natural recovery +150, Physical tolerance + 10%, Critical damage + 9%, Probability of magic attack when attacking<br /><br /><strong>Special Equipment</strong>:<br /><strong>Craft Guide Book </strong>- ATK increases with the difference between STR and DEX, and MATK with INT and CRT<br /><strong>Ring of Rush</strong> - DEX &amp; Accuracy &amp; Critical rate greatly decreases, Great ATK up by Lv<br /><strong>Myrica Wristlet</strong> - VIT up by 50% of Lv with Swords, Neutral R +5%<br /><strong>Ring of Fury</strong> - STR + 5, Melee pierce + 4%<br /><strong>Knight Gauntlet</strong> - ATK+30, ATK up by VIT (1/4 of VIT), HP+15% (use this only if it's slot)<br /><strong>Dark Hunter Eye</strong> - Crit dmg +4%, INT+2, Max HP-3% (same as above)<br /><strong>Disaster Stone</strong> - MaxHP -20%, Recoil +1%, ATK up based on VIT<br /><strong>Wild Ring</strong> - Melee to all elements +10% Element Resistance -10% MaxHP&amp;MP -10%<br /><br /><strong>Xtals</strong>:<br /><strong>Grapagos </strong>- STR + 3, VIT + 2, Heal received + 7%, Critical damage + 14% when equipped in a weapon<br /><strong>Sauro II - </strong>MaxHP +20%, MaxMP +20%, Exp +5%. On weapon, ATK +15%, MATK +20%, Melee pierce +5%, Magic pierce +5%<br /><strong>Cerberus </strong>- Critical rate -10, critical damage + 12%<br /><strong>Oritius </strong>- ATK + 9%, Auto HP recovery -20%<br /><strong>Telon</strong> - Autoskill -5%, Skill delay +1.5 sec, ATK +14%, Adds Autoskill +10%, Skill delay -0.5 sec on Special<br /><strong>Vatendeth </strong>- Melee +10% to earth (use on Fire element weapons)<br /><strong>Sturm </strong>- Melee to water + 10% (use on Wind element weapons)<br /><strong>Eisen </strong>- Melee to fire +10% (use on Water element weapons)<br /><strong>Aurumteus </strong>- Melee to wind +10% (use on Earth element weapons)<br /><strong>Halios </strong>- Melee to light +10% (use on Dark element weapons)<br /><strong>Argyros </strong>- Melee to dark +10% (use on Light element weapons)<br /><strong>Scorpia </strong>- Melee to neutral +10% (use on Neutral weapons)<br /><strong>Dorry</strong> - ATK + 6%, Rate cut -10%, ATK + 6% if equipped in body, Melee +300<br /><strong>Raton </strong>- Critical damage + 14%, MP consumption + 10%, ATK + 6%&nbsp;when equipped in additional<br /><strong>Iniliba </strong>- ATK +10% on Armor, MATK +10% on Armor, Damage cut chance by defense&nbsp;(Consumes autoskill)<br /><strong>Vida </strong>- ATK + 4%, Hate rise + 15%, ATK + 8% &amp; Hate rise -15%&nbsp;when equipped in additional<br /><strong>Belial </strong>- Melee pierce + 8%, ASPD + 10%, Critical damage + 7%&nbsp;when equipped in body<br /><strong>Beelzenoid </strong>- STR +1, Adds Critical damage +7% on Special, Double effect if STR &gt; 199<br /><strong>Pulis </strong>- Item delay -0.2seconds, Melee+200, when equipped on weapon ATK+5% Delay -0.5s Melee+300<br /><strong>Amatis</strong> -&nbsp;ATK +12%, HP Recovery -30%, DEF -60%. When equipped on armor, additional DEF +30%<br /><strong>White Fox</strong> - Water magic +5%, Melee +8% to Fire, Wind R -20%, when equipped on weapon, ATK &amp; MATK +8%<br /><strong>Wizard</strong> -&nbsp;MATK +8%, Magic R +18%, Small Light &amp; Dark magic &amp; Magic R up by INT <u>(for resistance set only)</u><br /><strong>Foxxus </strong>-&nbsp;Melee +6%, Delay -0.2 seconds, MaxMP -5%, When equipped on body Melee +10%<br /><br /><strong>Abilities:</strong><br /><strong>Quick Cool</strong> - Skill Delay -0.6s, ATK&amp;MATK - x% (5% to 1%, depending on ability level)<br /><strong>Quick Use</strong> - Item Delay -0.6s, item recovery - x% (depending on level)<br /><strong>Technique</strong> (mainly for ring of rush users)<br /><strong>Rate Cut&nbsp;<br />Melee Pierce<br />Attack<br />Strength/Critical/Agility/Dexterity/Vitality</strong><br /><br /><strong>AL xtals</strong>: <br /><strong>Cheltil</strong> - Skill delay -1 seconds, Item delay +0.5 seconds<br /><strong>Maelriel</strong> - ASPD + 10%, Cast time -10%, Delay -0.5 seconds<br /><strong>Mamonea</strong> - Critical damage + 5%, Critical rate + 10%, Magic resistance -10%<br /><strong>Arick </strong>- Critical Damage + 6%, Physical and Magic resistance -5%, Magic evasion -12%<br /><strong>Ouvel </strong>- ATK + 6%, MATK + 6%, MaxHP-10%, MaxMP-10%<br /><strong>Vatlia </strong>- ATK + 3%, Absolute evasion + 2%, MATK-3%<br /><strong>Zazel </strong>- ATK + 15, ATK + 2%, MATK + 30, MATK + 2%<br /><strong>Muscle </strong>- ATK + 10, ATK + 3%, HP natural recovery + 25%<br /><strong>Merario</strong> -&nbsp;VIT + 5, ATK + 2%, DEF + 140<br /><strong>Malti</strong> - Rate cut&nbsp;+ 10%, Meele pierce + 10%, Ailment resistance + 5%<br /><strong>Sauro II</strong> -&nbsp;Melee + 3% to all elements, whole magical power + 3%, Delay -0.5 seconds, Autoskill + 2%<br /><strong>Sauro III </strong>- Universal Element Melee +3% All Magic + 3% delay - 0.5 sec Autoskill +3% ATK&amp;MATK +30 Neutral Res +5%<br /><strong>Vatendeth</strong> -&nbsp;Melee R +10%, Magic R +10%, Hate rise -20%, Melee pierce +15%, Magic pierce +15%<br /><strong>Teo </strong>-&nbsp;ATK +2%, DEF +180, Critical damage +3%, Absolute evasion -5%<br /><strong>Gatekeeper</strong>&nbsp;(Al) - If [STR &gt; 350] then ATK +2% Melee +300 STR +3 If [INT &gt; 350] then MATK +2% MaxMP +5% INT +3 If [VIT &gt; 350] then MaxHP +5% Heal Reward +5% VIT +3 If [AGI &gt; 350] then Evasion +5% Counter on Evasion +5% AGI +3 If [DEX &gt; 350] then Item Delay -0.2s Skill Delay -0.2s Melee Pierce +2% Magic Pierce +2% DEX +3 If [CRT &gt; 350] then Critical damage +3% Absolute Evasion +2% Magic Evasion +2% CRT +3<br /><strong>Oritius </strong>(Al) -&nbsp;ATK +9% Melee to boss +2% Melee Pierce +3% MaxHP -15%<br /><strong>Vida</strong>&nbsp;(Al) -&nbsp;ATK +8%, MATK +8%, Autoskill -5%, Melee R -20%, Magic R -20%<br /><br /></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">The placement of AL xtals should be variations of this:</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;<img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://i.imgur.com/janvZYW.jpg" alt="" /></span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">You can either place green xtals in the middle and red on the sides (like seen on the picture) or red in the middle and green on the sides. However you do it is up to you, but with these setups you get 6 yellow lines, which is ideal for maximum damage. You can adjust them according to your preferences, like placing 5 green and 3 yellow lines, or all green lines, but it won't give you maximum damage.</span><br /><br /><br /><strong><span style="font-size: large;">Leveling</span><br /></strong><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="text-decoration: line-through;"><strong>120-200</strong> - I don't really think there are many options here, just do your MQ or, if you're determined to grind, grind megaroches in parties. Or basically anything that you can kill that gives decent exp.&nbsp;<br /><strong>200+</strong> - Now here's when the fun begins, as you now have pillar blade, your first AOE skill. Megas are still a way to go, but now you have more variety. Tigris gives decent exp, and you can exchange their drops for more exp. They also drop atleta ring, if you're lucky you might get a slotted one. If your DEF is decent they will deal 1 damage to you. You can also try nommars (and save your dirty gears until you're 240)<br /><strong>240+</strong> - Nommars definitely recommended and you have just unlocked the Dirty Gears quest. You can also try Baum Warriors, they shouldn't be too hard. But if they are, you can just explore and try grinding mobs which you can 1 shot with pillar.<br /><strong>260+ </strong>- With bloodthirst unlocked baum warriors shouldn't be too much of a challenge, if your build is VIT based you pretty much don't even have to worry about casting solid skin here. You can also try jacbos, you won't kill them in 1 hit so be careful, they hit pretty hard. Grind Nommars, Yardes, Third Eyes, whatever you're comfortable with.<br /><br /></span>Just grind Third Eyes<br /></span><strong><br /><br /><span style="font-size: large;">Tips and Tricks</span></strong><br /><span style="font-size: small; text-decoration: line-through;">The trick to spam tempest without meele attacking in between each Tempest (without using -ASPD gear) is to press down the movement stick immediately after Tempest's animation is finished (make sure to time it right so you don't move around).</span><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;There's no longer a need to do that as a function which lets you turn off auto attacking completely was added.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">To get as much potential out of your bloodthirst as possible, use regenerate without gladiator revita and switch your gears to make your max hp as high as possible (keep current hp at low values) and then use your bloodthirst. Using this metod on boss fights is not recommended, unless it's an easy boss.</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">As for farming, not gonna say much about it, because this isn't a spina making guide. But here's a tip, after getting Bloodthirst you can easily solo farm Sofys or Mezza. Socialize to get more farm opportunities.</span><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">Looking for a gladiator inspiration? Here are some links to gladiator oriented channels on youtube</span><br /><span style="font-size: small;">English version:&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCQ0HLmd9vnVX39BhP9oUD2A" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Tora</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCIVpKLj-__VoipW668k_t6w" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">EmiBaz</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-JxbsTwb7mt2SH7jCQympA" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Eaysley</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHZWSVNtQhMOvzc-TwwVZMw" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Vreya</a><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRGiQAFWnUonkDQKyX8VyJg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener"><br /></a><span style="font-size: small;">Japanese version:&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEbhPZwD9l1C27nX_J9kWqg/about" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">osieta girl</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCn89H9rKlCZ013tMo9hkHdg" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">匿名希望</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHM9EXz1zeOzqjVgO_L1yAw" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Mitsu 66</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnMcgugeJjUrFjJ6ZaMNshQ" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Sou (Square)</a><span style="font-size: small;">, </span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRxrxXbFxZI6aQvkqpO_g2g/feed" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">のん non</a><span style="font-size: small;">,&nbsp;</span><a style="font-size: small;" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-c-UERMcL0M31qhcLoa3Zw" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Asuramu<br /></a><span style="font-size: xx-small;">Message me if you want me to add your YT channel here.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">So that's about it. If you have any suggestions comment here, I'll gladly add any valuable info to this guide.<br /><br /></span></div>
